column2: Hot- sunny- mild breeze- no recent rain.
Sunny- moderate wave action and moderate boating activity; last rain on 8/6/86 was 2".
Partly sunny- warm- and no obvious algae.
Sunny and hot.  There is little boat traffic.
Partly cloudy- warm- little boat traffic.
Clear- sunny day-few boats- water has been very green for the past three weeks.
Lots of weeds- milfoil.  Water remarkably clear in weed beds.
Sunny and pleasant.  Perception due to weeds.
The lake level has remained close to 18 inches below the dam spillway all summer.
Weed situation real bad; perception due to weeds.
West Lobe of the lake turning green.
Although perception is 3- deep parts are okay for swimming.
The lake level is higher 13" since last fall.
Turning green on East Lobe of lake; West side (woodchuck alley).
So far no algae - weeds are minimal.
Since month of August the weeds grew a lot in low areas.
Public perception 3 in some parts and 5 in others.  Some areas of lake are green.
The floating weeds are main problem at this time.
Water color gray. small portions started- weeds growing.
Weeds started to grow fast in east lobe of lake.
Lake level high- water going over the dam.  Still cold - 60 degrees.
The lake level is high over dam.  The water color is gray.
Lake level is high over dam.  The water color is gray.

The reason Whitewater Lake is more murky this year is due to last winter's heavy ice and snow- which retarded the growth of weeds in the lake. Therefore- the lack of weeds made the lake more murky. I base this on 10 years + experience of lake measurements.
Large flock of gulls on bog.
Lost sight of secchi in weeds.  Bog still up.
